UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. Vernon R. LAWSON, Appellee. No. 7684. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Nov. 26, 1934. J. A. Carver, U. S. Atty., of Boise, Idaho. Hawley & Worth wine, of Boise, Idaho, for appellee.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and GARRE CUT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for appellant, and stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
